  "description": "<p>分类: <a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/category/misc-gadgets/\" rel=\"tag\">精彩杂录</a></p><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2013/07/25/european-commission-penguin-apple-e-book-agreement/\"><img src=\"http://www.blogcdn.com/cn.engadget.com/media/2013/07/ebooksapple-1374751324.jpg\" style=\"margin: 4px;\" /></a></div>\n\n<div><br />\n继<a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2012/12/13/amazon-wins-eu-e-book-pricing-battle-with-apple-and-major-publishers/\">去年 12 月</a>欧盟委员会接受了苹果及四家出版商为电子书价格松绑的提议之后，今天英国出版商 Penguin 终止与苹果合作的提议也终于被正式采纳了。和之前他们向美国司法部<a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2012/12/18/penguin-joins-publishers-settling-with-the-justice-department/\">承诺</a>的一样，Penguin 将会终止其与苹果及其他零售商间的代理协议，而且在未来五年内不会啓用「最惠国」条款。<br />\n<br />\n最重要的是，在接下来的两年内电子书零售商将可以自由控制 Penguin 旗下产品的价格及折扣。而随着价格操纵案中所涉及的各方面纷纷做出让步，欧盟委员「关于竞争的顾虑（competitive concerns）」也<a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2011/12/06/apple-and-major-publishers-investigated-for-e-book-price-rigging/\">总算</a>是得以消除了。<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n经由：<a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2013/07/25/european-commission-penguin-apple-e-book-agreement/\">Engadget</a>、<a href=\"http://www.reuters.com/article/2013/07/25/us-eu-penguin-idUSBRE96O0AM20130725\" target=\"_blank\">Reuters</a><br />\n引用来源：<a href=\"http://europa.eu/rapid/press-release_IP-13-746_en.htm\" target=\"_blank\">European Commission</a></div><p><h6 style=\"clear: both; padding: 8px 0 0 0; height: 2px; font-size: 1px; border: 0; margin: 0; padding: 0;\"></h6><a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2013/07/25/european-commission-penguin-apple-e-book-agreement/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent link to this entry\">此文章网址</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/forward/20676373/\" title=\"Send this entry to a friend via email\">转寄此文章</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2013/07/25/european-commission-penguin-apple-e-book-agreement/#comments\" title=\"View reader comments on this entry\">回应</a><hr size=\"1\" />", 
  "title": "欧盟委员会正式接受 Penguin 终止与苹果间电子书合作的提议"
 }
